# ADW (AI Developer Workflows) Configuration

# ==============================================================================
# Mode A: Claude Max Subscription (Default - Recommended for Interactive Use)
# ==============================================================================
# No configuration needed if you have Claude Max subscription.
# Claude Code will authenticate through your subscription automatically.
# This is the simplest setup for local development.

# ==============================================================================
# Mode B: API-Based Programmatic Execution (For Automation, CI/CD, Webhooks)
# ==============================================================================
# Required for headless/automated workflows where no interactive login is possible.
# Uncomment and set your API key:
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# ==============================================================================
# Claude Code Configuration
# ==============================================================================

# Optional: Claude Code CLI Path (auto-detected if not set)
# The ADW system will automatically find Claude Code in common locations:
# - CLAUDE_CODE_PATH environment variable (highest priority)
# - Output of `which claude`
# - ~/.claude/local/claude
# - /usr/local/bin/claude
# - /opt/homebrew/bin/claude
# Only set this if Claude Code is installed in a non-standard location:
# CLAUDE_CODE_PATH=/custom/path/to/claude

# Optional: Maintain working directory during bash operations
# CLAUDE_BASH_MAINTAIN_PROJECT_WORKING_DIR=true

# ==============================================================================
# GitHub Integration (Optional)
# ==============================================================================

# GitHub Personal Access Token (for GitHub issue operations)
# Required if using GitHub issues instead of beads for issue tracking
# Create at: https://github.com/settings/tokens
# Required scopes: repo (full control of private repositories)
# GITHUB_PAT=ghp_...

# ==============================================================================
# Beads Integration (Local Issue Tracking)
# ==============================================================================

# No configuration needed - beads uses local SQLite database
# Install beads: https://github.com/beadlework/beads
# Commands:
#   bd add "Task description" --type feature
#   bd ready
#   bd show <task-id>

# ==============================================================================
# Python Environment
# ==============================================================================

# PYTHONPATH is automatically managed by ADW workflows
# It includes src/ directory for imports
# PYTHONPATH=./src

# ==============================================================================
# ADW Workflow Configuration
# ==============================================================================

# These are automatically managed by the ADW system:
# - Worktree paths: trees/{adw_id}/
# - Port allocation: Deterministic based on ADW ID
# - State files: agents/{adw_id}/adw_state.json
# - Output files: agents/{adw_id}/{agent_name}/

# ==============================================================================
# Development Notes
# ==============================================================================

# 1. For local development, Mode A (subscription) is recommended
# 2. For CI/CD pipelines, use Mode B (API key)
# 3. ADW workflows automatically isolate state per execution
# 4. Worktrees provide full isolation for parallel development
# 5. See CLAUDE.md for complete ADW documentation
